            "body": "It seems not only related to quickfix. This create a normal buffer, it may need `restart` or refresh the list multiple times to reproduce. \n\n`j`/`k` should always print message? but sometime it don't.\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('WinScrolled', {\n  callback = function()\n    for winstr, change in pairs(vim.v.event) do\n      if change.topline == 0 or winstr == 'all' then return end\n      print(vim.uv.hrtime(), winstr, change.topline)\n    end\n  end,\n})\nCreateRandomBuffer = function()\n  vim.cmd [[%bw! | messages clear]]\n  vim.cmd('bot 1new|setl so=999 nu')\n  vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, false, vim.tbl_map(tostring, vim.fn.range(1, 1000)))\nend\nvim.cmd [[ \nnoremap <c-l> :lua CreateRandomBuffer()<CR> \nnoremap <c-r> :%bw!<bar>restart<CR>\n]]\n```",
